
[1]soot

   SOOT, n. A black substance formed by combustion, or disengaged from
   fuel in the process of combustion, rising in fine particles and
   adhering to the sides of the chimney or pipe conveying the smoke. Soot
   consists of oil, carbon and other substances. The soot of burnt pine
   forms lampblack.

   SOOT, v.t. To cover or foul with soot.
